com.github.wuic.engine

Enum EngineType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EngineType>
      • com.github.wuic.engine.EngineType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<EngineType>

    public enum EngineType
extends Enum<EngineType>

    This enumeration describes the different kind of Engine that may exist.

    In a chain of responsibility, the engines should be sorted following their EngineType. Sorting could be performed with this Comparable implementation. This way, a chain will always as the same behavior:

    • See if result is already cached or not.
    • Inspects all nuts and eventually transform them
    • Perform text compression on text files like scripts
    • Perform aggregation
    • Compress bytes

    Since:
    0.4.0
    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    Guillaume DROUET
